method.seeList:
CATIStrUseOpeningsMgr::GetStandardPositioningStrategyParms for the list of available positioning strategies and the parameter groups for each positioning strategy. Each parameter group object is identified and accessed by one of the following interfaces.
CATIStrUsePosSupportFace
Specifies the face of the reference element (if solid) to use.
CATIStrUsePosAxisAdjustment
Specifies a CKE parameter defining the contour rotation,,and U,,V shift.
CATIStrUseParameter
Specifies one CKE parameter.
CATIStrUseReference
Specifies one reference element.
CATIStrUseRefOffset
Specifies a reference element with a direction and an offset distance (CKE parameter).
CATIStrUsePosDualRef
Specifies a pair of reference elements.

NOTE: The volatile parameter group objects in this list are deleted automatically when all pointers to the objects are released. You should not release or delete these objects directly. ,
